      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Ben Mohr Herbster (1904-1984) was an American Protestant clergyman.  A native of Ohio, he was active in social issues 
	  such as civil rights.  In 1961 he was elected the first president of the United Church of Christ, a position he held for 
	  eight years.  He died in New York on December 16, 1984.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Ben M. Herbster Papers</emph> consists of printed material, sermons, addresses and other 
		 material.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
